data.title: Olympus updates labeling for bronchoscopes used with laser therapy worldwide. Clarification for safe usage.
data.description: Olympus Corporation, based in Center Valley, Pennsylvania, disclosed on October 31, 2025, a worldwide medical device corrective action aimed at enhancing understanding for the safe and efficient application of bronchoscopes in conjunction with laser therapy, argon plasma coagulation, or high-frequency procedures. This voluntary initiative is set to impact users globally and aims to ensure proper usage of these devices.

data.title: Magnificent 7 tech stocks drive S&P 500 up 40% since April lows. Market value now over $22 trillion; Nvidia hits $5 trillion.
data.description: The fascination of Wall Street with mega-cap tech companies remains strong as the S&P 500 achieved its sixth consecutive month of growth, surging over 40% since hitting post-tariff lows in April. The focus continues to be on the "Magnificent Seven" which includes Nvidia Corp., Microsoft Corp., Apple Inc., Amazon.com Inc., Alphabet Inc., Meta Platforms Inc., and Tesla Inc. These tech giants now hold a collective market value exceeding $22 trillion, with Nvidia standing out by reaching an unprecedented $5 trillion valuation, solidifying its position as the most valuable company globally. data.title: Accuray Inc. announced inducement award to new CEO under NASDAQ Listing Rules on Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: Madison, Wisconsin – On October 31, 2025, Accuray Incorporated disclosed equity inducement awards in compliance with NASDAQ rules to Stephen La Neve, the newly appointed Chief Executive Officer. These awards were provided as part of an effort to attract Mr. La Neve to the company. Accuray Incorporated is listed as ARAY on the NASDAQ stock exchange.

data.title: Amgen's Q4 2025 dividend declared at $2.38 per share, to be paid on Dec 12th.
data.description: Amgen, headquartered in Thousand Oaks, California, revealed today that its Board of Directors has approved a dividend of $2.38 per share for the fourth quarter of 2025. This dividend is scheduled to be disbursed on December 12, 2025, to all shareholders of record as of the closing date indicated.

data.title: Mueller Water Products to release Q4 and full year 2025 financial results on Nov 6; conference call on Nov 7 at 10am ET. Visit their website for more info.
data.description: Mueller Water Products, Inc. (NYSE: MWA) is set to announce its financial results for the fourth quarter and full year ending on September 30, 2025, after the closing of U.S. markets on Thursday, November 6, 2025. A conference call discussing earnings and business outcomes will be held on Friday, November 7, 2025, at 10:00 a.m. ET. The webcast can be accessed through the Investor Relations section of the company's website at www.muellerwaterproducts.com. After the call, an archive of the webcast will be accessible for approximately 90 days.

data.title: Foresight Psychology, PLLC provides testing services for standardized exams like GRE, MCAT, GMAT, LSAT, and ACT, and SAT nationwide.
data.description: Foresight Psychology, based in San Diego, made an announcement on October 31, 2025, regarding the launch of psychological testing services. These services cater to individuals who require accommodations on standardized exams such as the GRE, GMAT, etc. By providing these services, Foresight Psychology aims to level the playing field for test-takers and help them showcase their true potential. This initiative is designed to assist a significant number of individuals in maximizing their performance in standardized exams.

data.title: The Beryl Institute awards grants for 4 studies on patient experience improvement in healthcare.
data.description: The Beryl Institute, a worldwide community of healthcare professionals committed to enhancing the human experience in healthcare, will be funding four research studies focused on patient experience improvement. The announcement was made in Nashville, Tennessee on October 31, 2025. This initiative aims to support research efforts in this area and ultimately enhance patient care.

data.title: Tentative agreement reached between CUPE 3261 and University of Toronto Press & Bookstore for 100+ workers, avoiding strike.
data.description: In Toronto, the Canadian Union of Public Employees (CUPE) 3261 has successfully negotiated a tentative agreement for over 100 employees working in the warehouse and retail sectors of the University of Toronto Press and Bookstore. This agreement, if approved by both CUPE members and the employer, will prevent a potential strike at the University of Toronto, which serves as the country's oldest university publisher, distributor, and retailer.

data.title: Cleveland's DigitalC initiative connects 7,000 homes and 17,000 residents, 85% towards 2025 goal. #digitalinclusion
data.description: Cleveland's citywide broadband initiative, led by DigitalC, has successfully connected almost 7,000 homes and over 17,000 residents. This progress puts them at 85% of their 2025 goal. According to news released on October 31, 2025, DigitalC, a nonprofit chosen by the City of Cleveland for this project, continues to make significant strides in providing internet access to the community.

data.title: ELGi to showcase compressed air solutions for automotive aftermarket at SEMA Show 2025, Booth #12639 in Las Vegas.
data.description: ELGi Compressors USA (ELGi) is set to showcase its lineup of air compressors and air treatment systems tailored for the automotive aftermarket sector at the SEMA Show in Las Vegas, Booth #12639. The exhibition will feature various products geared towards the industry, such as the EN15 Duplex (20 hp) rotary screw air compressor, the AB55 (75hp) oil-free rotary screw air compressor, the D185T4F tow-behind portable air compressor, and the AR N Series refrigerated air dryer. Attendees can explore these offerings designed specifically for the automotive segment.
